      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the S54B32 high-pressure die-cast iron block engine. This 3.2L inline-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and double VANOS continuous variable valve timing to produce 333 hp with a 7,900 RPM redline. Crucially, the rod bearings have been replaced and the VANOS unit has been overhauled with uprated seals. The power is managed by a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and an M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis is structurally sound, featuring a proactive subframe reinforcement kit to mitigate floor pan fatigue. Suspension remains tight with refreshed control arm bushings and Bilstein dampers. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina consistent with 'good' condition, the drivetrain remains exceptionally linear and responsive. An ideal specimen for the purist seeking analog feedback and peak atmospheric performance.",
